Package com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.tree

Class BSTSimple<Key extends Comparable<Key>,Value>

java.lang.Object
com.phasmidsoftware.dsaipg.adt.symbolTable.tree.BSTSimple<Key,Value>
Type Parameters:
Key - the type of keys maintained by this BST. Must be comparable.
Value - the type of mapped values.
All Implemented Interfaces:
ImmutableSymbolTable<Key,Value>, ST<Key,Value>, BST<Key,Value>, BstDetail<Key,Value>
public class BSTSimple<Key extends Comparable<Key>,Value> extends Object implements BstDetail<Key,Value>
A simple implementation of a Binary Search Tree (BST) that maps keys to values. The class allows basic BST operations such as insertion, retrieval, deletion, in-order traversal, and calculation of depths.

The BST implicitly assumes that all keys are unique and comparison of keys will determine their order in the tree structure.

    • BSTSimple

      public BSTSimple(Map<Key,Value> map)
      Constructs a Binary Search Tree (BST) by initializing it as empty and then populating it with the key-value pairs from the provided map. The keys from the map are inserted in a randomized order.
      Parameters:
      map - a map containing key-value pairs to be inserted into the BST; keys must be unique, and the map cannot be null.
